## Placement of the Doxee Lightning component
To call the Doxee components directly from Salesforce, you first have to configure which pages or objects and at which position the call should happen. To enable this, Doxee provides its Lightning components, which can be inserted on the corresponding pages by using the Salesforce Lightning App Builder. The following is an example of how a document creation process can be inserted on the contact object page. First, you must launch Salesforce Lightning App Builder from the Salesforce Setup Menu.

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)Salesforce Lightning App Builder

Select the page you want to modify. In our example we select *Contact Record Page.*

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)Salesforce Lightning App Builder - Page Selection

After selecting the page, click *Edit to *get to the actual App Builder page.

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)Salesforce Lightning App Builder - Editing the Page 

Now you can use the normal Salesforce board tools to modify the page, add new sections, add new tabs, and more. In our example, another tab named *YourComfort *was added on the *Related, Details *level. The name can be freely assigned here. 

Now, from the Salesforce palette on the left, drag the Lightning component *Doxee Workplace *into the space of the new tab.

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)Doxee Lightning component selection 

Now the Lightning component is positioned. In the next subchapter, this Lightning component will be configured.

## Configuration of the Doxee Lightning component 
After placing the component, the corresponding parameters are set. This happens after the Doxee Lightning component has been selected in the right pane 

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

Inserted Doxee Lightning component 

In the first field "*Process*" the process to be called is selected. Doxee offers several preconfigured process flows (e.g. template selection, interactive editing, PDF preview). In general, it should be emphasized that the Doxee Process Designer gives you the possibility to create your own processes graphically in a flexible way. 

In the following fields, the user can select from the existing Doxee Queries, which the user has created according to the explanations in the previous chapter. The first query corresponds to the main query, which also gets the ID of the selected object from the corresponding page. The following queries refer to the result of a previous query. 

The lower configuration settings determine the size of the used area.
